    {
      "id": "g0A6RZ-RfhfUS8ElXMOgv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 327,
      "y": 223,
      "width": 1010.706787109375,
      "height": 354.2246093750001,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 680505638,
      "version": 634,
      "versionNonce": 1898435174,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774061279790,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is finetuning?\n\n\n- Pretrained LLM knows the grammer, reasoning, facts\n-   Finetuning means we continue training the model for our own specific task\n-  In finetuning all the weights will get updated based on our training\n\n\n\nPre-traning : they use huge data available , Model learns the language \nFinetuning : Continue training on the dataset which is task -specific ,Model adapts to it\nInstruction : Fine tune on the instruction-response pair. Models learns the response directions.\n",
      "fontSize": 21.79843750000001,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What is finetuning?\n\n\n- Pretrained LLM knows the grammer, reasoning, facts\n-   Finetuning means we continue training the model for our own specific task\n-  In finetuning all the weights will get updated based on our training\n\n\n\nPre-traning : they use huge data available , Model learns the language \nFinetuning : Continue training on the dataset which is task -specific ,Model adapts to it\nInstruction : Fine tune on the instruction-response pair. Models learns the response directions.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
