    {
      "id": "wT9bK5cUgCs2qm0bRWs2z",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -150.6974088828996,
      "y": 2371.1502520358217,
      "width": 1042.914182856322,
      "height": 950,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "af",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 205190694,
      "version": 905,
      "versionNonce": 485588454,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774064498621,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Evaluation:\n\n1. ROUGUE ->( Recall oriented understudy for Gisting Evaluation)\n\n-> Refrence Summary: The cat sat on the mat\n-> Model output -> Cat is on the mat\n\n\nIt is used for summarization, measures how much reference is covered.\n\n\n2. BLEU ( Bilingual Evaluation understudy)\n\n-> where they try to match word by words\n\n-> Machine Translation\n\n-> Refrence Summary: The cat sat on the mat\n-> Model output -> Cat is on the mat (Medium Score)\n\n\n\n3. METEOR (Imporoved version of BLUE)\n\n-> Instead of matching exact words, it tried to understand the synonyms of the words\n\n-> run , running(human evaluation)\n\n\n4. BERT Score ( Semantic Understanding)\n\n\n- Reference : The man in eating\n- Model output : The person is having food\n\n\nBLUE/ROUGUE -> very less score\nBERT : Understand context and semantics ( Very good)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Evaluation:\n\n1. ROUGUE ->( Recall oriented understudy for Gisting Evaluation)\n\n-> Refrence Summary: The cat sat on the mat\n-> Model output -> Cat is on the mat\n\n\nIt is used for summarization, measures how much reference is covered.\n\n\n2. BLEU ( Bilingual Evaluation understudy)\n\n-> where they try to match word by words\n\n-> Machine Translation\n\n-> Refrence Summary: The cat sat on the mat\n-> Model output -> Cat is on the mat (Medium Score)\n\n\n\n3. METEOR (Imporoved version of BLUE)\n\n-> Instead of matching exact words, it tried to understand the synonyms of the words\n\n-> run , running(human evaluation)\n\n\n4. BERT Score ( Semantic Understanding)\n\n\n- Reference : The man in eating\n- Model output : The person is having food\n\n\nBLUE/ROUGUE -> very less score\nBERT : Understand context and semantics ( Very good)",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
